{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=2003 |Team=South Carolina Gamecocks |Image=South Carolina Gamecocks wordmark.svg |ImageSize=150 |Conference=Southeastern Conference |Division=Eastern Division |ShortConference=SEC |CoachRank= |APRank= |BCSRank= |Record=5-7 |ConfRecord=2-6 |HeadCoach=[[Lou Holtz]] |DefCoach= |StadiumArena=[[Williams-Brice Stadium]] (c. 80,250, grass) |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{2003 SEC football standings}} The '''2003 South Carolina Gamecocks football team''' represented the [[University of South Carolina]] in the [[Southeastern Conference]] during the [[2003 NCAA Division I-A football season]]. The Gamecocks were led by [[Lou Holtz]] in his fifth season as USC head coach and played their home games in [[Williams-Brice Stadium]] in [[Columbia, South Carolina]]. The Gamecocks did not finish the season bowl-eligible.
